KILMOREY MAUSOLEUM OPEN HOUSE - 23 SEPTEMBER 2018
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    It all sounded rather romantic. She was Priscilla, the daughter of
    a dashing sea captain and associate of Lord Nelson. He was Jack,
    the enigmatic son of the Irish peerage, and student of the occult.
    They fell in love when he was 53 years old, a peer of the realm and
    married with children and she was a blushing 20-year-old - and his
    legal ward. At the time it was an absolute scandal - a veritable
    cause c&#233;l&#232;bre! There was much to gossip about for the
    antimacassar set of early Victorian society!

