COUNCIL SUPPORTS NEW BREXIT VOTE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Members voted in favour of a motion on 11th September to support
    the growing campaign for a 'People's Vote' on the future
    Brexit deal.

    At the Full Council meeting, Cllr Richard Pyne, Councillor for
    North Richmond, proposed a motion that voices the Council's concern
    over the country leaving the EU and agrees that the British people
    should have a say on the terms negotiated.

